{%- comment -%}
  Product Color Swatches — renders small color circles from variant options.
  Reads the "Color" option from product.options_with_values.

  Used ONLY in card-product.liquid (collection cards, featured collections,
  related-products). The PDP uses `product-variant-picker.liquid`, which
  has its own metafield branch. Keeping the card-context lookup native-only
  avoids the N+1 hit of reading per-variant metafields for every card on a
  paginated collection page (a 24-product page with 16 variants each was
  doing ~3,072 inner iterations and ~384 metafield fetches).

  Each swatch is picked from two sources, in priority order:

    1. Shopify's native option-value swatch (OS 2.0 Color option type).
       When the merchant configures a color or image swatch in the
       admin product editor, `option.selected_value.swatch.color` /
       `.image` is populated automatically. This is the canonical
       source and needs no theme intervention.

    2. Name→hex lookup for ~20 common English/multilingual color words.
       Last-resort only — for stores that haven't configured the native
       swatch yet. Merchants who want richer colors should configure
       the native OS 2.0 swatch in the product editor (recommended).

  Renders nothing if no "Color" option exists.

  Accepts:
  - product: {Object} Shopify product
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign color_option = nil
  for option in product.options_with_values
    assign option_name_lower = option.name | downcase
    if option_name_lower == 'color' or option_name_lower == 'colour' or option_name_lower == 'renk' or option_name_lower == 'couleur' or option_name_lower == 'farbe'
      assign color_option = option
      break
    endif
  endfor
-%}

{%- if color_option and color_option.values.size > 0 -%}
  <div class="kt-swatches" aria-label="{{ color_option.name }}">
    {%- for value in color_option.values -%}
      {%- liquid
        # 1. Native OS 2.0 swatch on the option value. `value` here is
        #    a ProductOptionValue object when the option is of Color
        #    type; `.swatch.color` is the merchant-configured hex,
        #    `.swatch.image` is the uploaded variant image.
        assign swatch_bg = nil
        assign swatch_image_url = nil
        if value.swatch != blank
          if value.swatch.color != blank
            assign swatch_bg = value.swatch.color
          endif
          if value.swatch.image != blank
            assign swatch_image_url = value.swatch.image | image_url: width: 64
          endif
        endif

        # 2. Keyword fallback — last resort only.
        if swatch_bg == nil and swatch_image_url == nil
          assign color_lower = value | downcase | strip
          case color_lower
            when 'black'
              assign swatch_bg = '#1a1a1a'
            when 'white', 'arctic white'
              assign swatch_bg = '#faf9f6'
            when 'beige'
              assign swatch_bg = '#e8dccc'
            when 'brown'
              assign swatch_bg = '#6b4e31'
            when 'gray', 'grey'
              assign swatch_bg = '#808080'
            when 'navy'
              assign swatch_bg = '#2c3e50'
            when 'silver'
              assign swatch_bg = '#c0c0c0'
            when 'orange'
              assign swatch_bg = '#d35400'
            when 'green'
              assign swatch_bg = '#27ae60'
            when 'burgundy'
              assign swatch_bg = '#800020'
            when 'red'
              assign swatch_bg = '#c0392b'
            when 'blue'
              assign swatch_bg = '#2980b9'
            when 'yellow'
              assign swatch_bg = '#f1c40f'
            when 'pink'
              assign swatch_bg = '#e91e8c'
            when 'cream'
              assign swatch_bg = '#FFFDD0'
            when 'ivory'
              assign swatch_bg = '#FFFFF0'
            when 'walnut'
              assign swatch_bg = '#5D432C'
            when 'oak'
              assign swatch_bg = '#d2b48c'
            when 'espresso'
              assign swatch_bg = '#3C2415'
            when 'charcoal'
              assign swatch_bg = '#36454F'
            when 'midnight'
              assign swatch_bg = '#191970'
            else
              assign swatch_bg = '#a8a29e'
          endcase
        endif
      -%}

      {%- if swatch_image_url -%}
        <span
          class="kt-swatches__dot kt-swatches__dot--image"
          style="background-image: url('{{ swatch_image_url }}');"
          title="{{ value | escape }}"
          aria-label="{{ value | escape }}"
        ></span>
      {%- else -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          `swatch_bg` resolves from one of three sources, in order:
            1. value.swatch.color   — Shopify-validated hex
            2. (no longer present in card context — see header comment)
            3. The keyword fallback table above OR the grey default
          Source 1 is system-validated; source 3 is theme-controlled
          hex literals. The `else` branch in the case table assigns
          `'#a8a29e'` (a literal). So `swatch_bg` is always a known-
          safe CSS color string. We still pipe it through `| escape`
          before output as defense-in-depth — if a future change
          introduces a path that lets a merchant-named option flow
          through (e.g. a metafield path), this protects the style
          attribute from CSS injection via `; expression()` legacy
          vectors and ensures Theme Store automated audits don't
          flag the un-escaped settings interpolation.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <span
          class="kt-swatches__dot"
          style="background-color: {{ swatch_bg | escape }};"
          title="{{ value | escape }}"
          aria-label="{{ value | escape }}"
        ></span>
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}
